Vercel Web Analytics Installation Completed Successfully

## Summary
Installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Package version installed: Latest available version from npm registry

### 2. Configuration
Modified: `frontend/app/layout.js`
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout
- This follows the Next.js App Router pattern as documented in the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide

### 3. Updated Dependencies
- `package.json`: Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies
- `package-lock.json`: Updated with the new package and its dependencies

## Implementation Details
The Analytics component was placed at the end of the body tag (after the footer) following Next.js App Router best practices. This ensures:
- The component is loaded on all pages of the application
- Analytics tracking is initialized properly
- No interference with existing layout structure
- Optimal performance with the component loading last

## Verification Steps Completed
✓ Build successful: `npm run build` completed without errors
✓ Linter ran: No new errors introduced (only pre-existing warnings remain)
✓ Project structure preserved: All existing code and functionality remain intact
✓ Framework-specific configuration: Used Next.js App Router specific import path (`@vercel/analytics/next`)

## Next Steps
To activate Web Analytics:
1. Deploy the application using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
3. Data collection will begin once enabled in the dashboard

## Notes
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation exactly
- Used the framework-specific import (`@vercel/analytics/next`) for optimal performance in Next.js
- The Analytics component is rendered on all pages through the root layout
- No additional configuration is required in the code
